text: Gosh! I love these girls so much! 7 years have passed but they are still this chaotic and playful when together. It's true though, it's best when it's the four of them! They've grown so much in that 7 years. And they are all getting gorgeous and gorgeous each year! They are all so blooming and looking so mature now. Except when they want to look cute though. Hahaha! But that's what i love about them. BLACKPINK, you've been part of every BLINKS lives for 7 years. We may not always tell you this, but you've been a BIG PART of us. Like we can't imagine ourselves not being Blinks and not being able to see and support you everyday. You've been our inspiration, some even made you their strengths during hard times. You don't know how much impact you have made in our lives. We just want you to know that WE BLINKS LOVE YOU SO MUCH BLACKPINK! BLACKPINK AND BLINKS WILL STAY TOGETHER AS YOU LONG AS TIME ALLOWS US TO. But as for me, i will love and cherish the 4 of you in my heart forever! I love you Lisa, Jennie, Jisoo and Rosé! Always remember, Blinks will always have your back! HAPPY 7TH ANNIVERSARY JENCHULICHAENG! HAPPY BIRTHDAY BLACKPINK! BLACKPINK BLACKPINK BLACKPINK! BLINK BLINK BLINK! FOREVER! WE LOVE YOU! 💜💙💛🤍

author: @studykuma3862
text:
saying goodbye to my Unnies, feels damn heartbreaking.. I discovered BLACKPINK, 4 years ago, and since then, I've been a hardcore BLINK. Personally, for me, BLACKPINK isn't just all about their music; it's them. Its JENNIE unnie, JISOO unnie, ROSÉ unnie and LISA unnie. They are my inspiration, my comfort buddies, my motivators, my mood uplifters, my support system, my life guides, my sisters, my IDOLS. They are a part of who I am. If I'm a strong, self sufficient, independent and HAPPY person today, the credits go to BLACKPINK. They taught me to love myself and be proud of who I am.

Happy 7th Anniversary to BLACKPINK. I'm so proud of my unnies, and I'm so grateful to be a part of this amazing fandom. Proud to be a BLINK.

Thanks for everything BLACKPINK. You were, are, and will forever be my idols. 

XOXO, Luna <3

author: @feartheunknown__
text: First of all, except Rosé, all the members are getting the values they deserve, at least they started to get it. Although Rosé's solo came out about two years ago, Jisoo's solo surpassed it. Now, Rosé's outfits have been changed very little compared to the other members at concerts, and her makeup has been stripped off with a distorted eyeliner. Looking at the other members' make-up, Rosé's make-up looks very pale. Also, despite being the lead dancer, she was almost always kept in the background. Despite 4 years of training, she dances incredibly. Another issue is that although he is the main vocalist, there are very few songs where he hits high notes, we can even say 2-3. Although Rosé has an amazing voice, she has a company that doesn't use it. It should really be realized that Rosé is no longer valued. Now, I want to be in the foreground for a little bit, to be careful with her make-up and outfit, and most importantly, to hit high notes as the main vocal. I love every member but I wrote this because what happened to Rosé was more sloppy. Greetings from Turkiye.

author: @Dann_ross
text:
Dear BLACKPINK

I don't really know how to start writing this letter, but first of all, I want to tell the girls that I am very happy and proud of everything they do for BLINKS, we know that they always give their best on stage... So I mean that

Jisoo you are the funniest and prettiest girl I know, you always make me laugh and smile, your acting skills are so amazing, I hope to see you act again, I love you so much Chu.

Jennie, your smile is my witness, how can you be so pretty and cute? Your rap skills are everything, you are an amazing girl. I love you so much, Jendeukie..

Rosé, girl, how can your voice be so sweet and soothing? Your incredible voice takes me to paradise. (I need to hear your high notes more to keep living) I love you so much, I can only say how much I admire you, you are my main motivation to achieve my dreams, I went crazy for you, (I love you so much) Rosie Posie.

Lisa, I can only say that you are the main motivation to achieve my dreams, your dance skills drive me crazy, you are an incredible girl, I love you so much Limario.
❤❤

author: @bretxavier9305
text:
Sorry, but y’all like to paint Blackpink as “not for kids” as the girls literally act like children, hold stuffed animals, are on a set holding said stuffed animals in a childish manor, as the group transitions from regular font to a bubble child looking one, cartoons of their characters all over the place, childish voice…please.

This is such a sad excuse to use when parents are angry that their children see the members acting provocatively, after the moms did their research and saw childish looking content for Blackpink.

They talk to their fans like literal children, in addition to selling toys, child like clothing, showing cartoons, selling stuffed animals, holding them, playing with them, showcasing them and using a child’s voice.

You’re either in favour of kids seeing inappropriate things for their ages or you’re not. 
Simple as that.

Blackpink’s either encouraging kids to come or they’re playing into the fëtïsh of a young prepubescent being out there for the men.

You can’t tell a parent that it’s their fault for their child attending a concert where a woman gets down on all fours with her cheeks hanging out, twerks, shows tons of cleavage, nearly exposes their l*bia and goes butt to butt when nearly all of Blackpink’s content is in this exact format of bubbling, with cartoons and flowers and speaking like a child.

Either you’re infantilizing the group (though the groups infantilizing themselves would be more appropriate) or you’re of the mindset that children should see such things or you’re in agreement that Blackpink should act grown *always* not just when they want to get down and nasty and sl*tty.

There could be an argument for the western world, with the inclusion of South Korea, seeing female children’s things as more s-xual on a woman… however that absolutely doesn’t absolve Blackpink of their own advertisements, their image, their marketing and their actions.

They’re grown woman and know what they’re doing.

Don’t you think it’s embarrassing, h*ll humiliating at this point, to go be twerking on all fours, cheeks out, l*bia hanging, and then you go backstage to see little 8 year old Suzy trynna take a picture with you after the concert?

That’s so disgusting.

There is a reason woman and girls are separated with clothing and styles.
This is more so applied to all adults and children.
They look different because ones mature and ready to mate, ready to understand and knows better and the others a child who can’t understand anything but can soak everything up likes a sponge to be influenced later on.

Women don’t act like this.

They don’t grab stuffed animals and squeal. They don’t wear short tiny, barely there “skirts” that show cheeks and then turn around pretending that you didn’t realize your cheeks were out and ask for a blanket to cover yourself when you sit down. (We’ve seen it all before on stage…remember?)
They don’t hop on every childish thing out there or play with children’s toys.

Yes, sometimes adults and children overlap in certain fields, however Blackpink go *heavy* into it.  To the point it crosses the line.

Either accept that you’re grown and embrace it fully or stay in the childish lane completely.

You can’t be hopping back and forth when you’re influencing so many people, getting children to imitate you as you literally scream at he crowd to “twerk”

This isn’t a case where you give the excuse of them being able to “do whatever they want”

You picked up the title of being an idol/celebrity/whatever and wanted it.that means you’ve certain responsibilities.

Jennie even partially admitted in an interview where she discussed “opening doors” for others to “be themselves”

So what is it? You’re a sl*tty adult or a coy woman who doesn’t want to show any skin as you talk as if you’re speaking to children? 

This goes for all the members as someone who likes their music. 

Don’t want to be a “fan” because it’s dense to idolize someone for simply making music…which they don’t really “make” much anyways.
Someones actions are something to idolize and Blackpink’s actions aren’t up there to be idolized.

They act as if they should be idolized as they take on all kind of roles to “lead the future” for planet saving, helping kids and such.

The groups at a turning point of needing to pick a lane.

You go forward being a grown woman or you go forward acting like a grown woman who talks to children.
Which, by the way, grown woman don’t tend to show it all off. You can’t ask for “equality” when you show 90% of your body and men show at most 30%

The group wants to be mature and for grown ups, be it. Don’t add all the children like noises, toys, ads, get ups etc.
Grown woman never devolved into childhood as they push 30.

You’ve to wonder how many minors and children are watching this currently, because of all the childish crap Blackpink pushes.

Blackpink’s kept the childish image thing for a while, but it’s almost as if they caught on to other kpop groups getting more attention for their “youthful” images and decided to turn it up a notch by adding more.

text: 블링크 7주년 축하해 널 위한 말 매일매일이 슬프고 지쳐 너 덕분에 아는 너의 영상만 보고 웃어주는 영상 하나만으로도 행복해 그래서 내가 당신을 얼마나 사랑하는지 말하려고 이 글을 씁니다. 지수 당신은 항상 블랙핑크의 어머니이고 우리와 사랑을 나누어줘서 정말 고마워요 제니 당신은 최고의 래퍼이고 저는 무슨 말을 해야할지 모르겠습니다. 너의 미소를 사랑하고 또한 우리를 행복하게 해주셔서 대단히 감사합니다, 나의 작은 다람쥐 장미님은 정말 아름답습니다 그리고 당신은 사랑을 나누어 주셔서 대단히 감사합니다 리사 당신을 잊지 않을 것입니다 당신은 블랙 핑크의 막내입니다 ,조그마한 발걸음,춤 잘추고 매일매일 웃게 해주셔서 너무 감사하고 오히려 블링크와 함께 사랑 나눠주신 모든 분들께 진심으로 감사드립니다. 행복하고 울고 사랑에 울고 벌써 7주년이라 행복해 기억해 사랑해 우리 별들🌟✨❤

author: @satgotlizz
text: As a supporter of Blackpink since 2016, I'm incredibly proud of all four of you. I knew you would be successful since you were YG's first girl group since 2NE1, but I never expected something like this. I've watched you grow from girls with a strong passion to perform into women with an even stronger passion to perform for your millions of fans. When I stood in that crowd at HYDE park after waiting for so many years and missing every opportunity to see you, I couldn't help but break down. Especially when Boombayah played. I looked around at the huge crowd of hundreds of thousands of people, all there for blackpink. All there for those four humble, fun, charismatic girls that I loved and supported for all these years. It gave me goosebumps. I love you all so so so much and I'm so grateful for having the four of you as an influence in my life. Happy 7th anniversary, Blackpink. And happy 7th anniversary of me being a blink. 🖤🩷

author: @studioversionshoom
text: Me acuerdo cuando conocí a Blackpink en la cuarentena (2020) en ese entonces no estaba tan metido en la industria de la música, hasta no sabía q era un álbum, me acuerdo que las canciones que escuchaba eran, DDU DU DDU DU y BOOMBAYAH, y luego descubrí lo que era un álbum jajaja y me metí a escuchar todo su discografía, en ese entonces había salido THE ALBUM hace unas semanas y no paraba de escuchar sus canciones, AMEE LAS CANCIONES DE BLACKPINK, jamás me cansaron, lamentablemente me había echo blink cuando las pinks estuvieron 2 años sin un Comeback y no había estado nunca en un Comeback de las 4, solo había estado en el de Rosé y Lisa, me acuerdo cuando reproducía a cada rato las presentaciones que tenían o cuando veía la serie de BLACKPINK HOUSE jaja...  Me acuerdo que cuando habían sacado el teaser de BORN PINK, no me lo podía creer era la primera vez en mí vida de blink jajaja que iba a estar presente en un Comeback, me puse tan felizzz, siempre voy a estar agradecido de a ver conocido a BLACKPINK, me ayudaron mucho en el 2020 que estaba pasando por una situación muy difícil y cuando escuchaba sus canciones me olvidaba de absolutamente todo por lo que estaba pasando, LAS QUIERO MUCHO CHICAS Y FELIZ 7 ANIVERSARIO

author: @오공본드-w9i
text: 리사야 오빠는 수없이 보아왔다. 그렇게 이쁘다고 사랑받고 인기많던 애들도 싹퉁머리 없는 거 보이거나 사회적 물의를 일으키거나 그러면 한순간에 어디로 갔는지 보이지 않고 사라지더라. 그리고 또 하나 어떤 그룹을 탈퇴하면 또 사라져가더라. 더는 욕심내지 말고 블랙핑크로 살다가 블랙핑크로 끝내렴. 그래야 먼 훗날 한시대를 풍미했던 그룹으로 남아 영원히 음악과 영상으로 남을거야. 과거 유명했던 가수나 그룹들 생각해봐 다 그 모습 그대로 기억에 남아 마무리해줬기에 기억되는거야. 아무리 새로운게 나아보여도 지금것이 가장 좋은거야. 혹시 싸우더라도 잘 화해하고 옆에서 잘 화해시켜주고 성인들 답게 분위기 조절 잘해서 힘내길 바란다. 비틀즈도 따로 흩어져서 활동하면 인기가 없어지는거야. 나이가 많아져서 그만둔다면 모르겠는데 탈퇴해서 따로 활동하는 것은 좋아보이지 않아. 개인 무대도 블랙핑크 맴버로 있기 때문에 사람들이 봐주고 인기있는거야. 멤버들 전부 좀 지쳤으면 한 1~2년 쉬었다가 다시해도 괜찮아

author: @Lalilou_b
text:
There are no words to describe how much I love these 4 wonderful girls. They came into my life just when I needed to learn to love myself and believe in my dreams. 
They are so important to me, it's like a family.
I love them so much for everything they do and all they are. I am grateful to have known them for a little over 5 years and I feel lucky to be part of the blinks.
When I think back to those years of following them, watching them grow and become the global stars they are, I am so moved. 
I also realize that they have grown up well and now they look fulfilled and happy with their careers. I wish them every success even though they have already made history. 
I will always remember them as an example of success and work. They are living proof that with determination, talent and hope, we can succeed in making our dreams a reality. 
During these years, I have evolved with them and what I find beautiful is that despite their success and their statue of the biggest girlsband in the world, they remain humble and show us a little more each time who they are : beautiful women inside and outside, full of talent and merit, full of smile and courage. 
I admire them so much to continue to be themselves no matter what. 
I wish them all the happiness in the world and I hope with all my heart that they will continue to follow their dreams and find the peace. 
Jisoo, Jennie, Rosé, Lisa, I love you to the moon and back, you're my hope, my hapiness, my family, my safe place et I'll always supporting you, no matter your choises. 
I'm so thankfull you have no idea. 
You are my models, thank you for existing and make my life better ❤️
And I hope that, beyond your phenomenal success, you are happy in your life cause you deserve it so far 💕

Love you all from my heart and my soul, 

This is a letter, from me to BLACKPINK.

author: @DavidMARINELLI-r9w
text:
Chères Lisa, Jennie, Jisoo et Rosé,

Joyeux 7ème anniversaire, Blackpink ! 🎉🖤💖 Votre incroyable parcours au cours de ces sept années a illuminé les scènes du monde entier et touché les cœurs de millions de fans, dont le mien.

Vos chansons sont bien plus que de simples mélodies ; elles sont des chefs-d'œuvre rythmés qui éveillent nos émotions et nous font danser au rythme de votre talent unique. Chacun de vos solos est un témoignage de vos compétences et de votre individualité éblouissantes, montrant à quel point vous brillez non seulement en tant que groupe, mais aussi en tant qu'artistes solos exceptionnelles.

Votre unicité en tant que groupe est indéniable. Chaque membre apporte une énergie et une personnalité spéciale qui s'harmonisent parfaitement pour créer le phénomène Blackpink. Lisa, Jennie, Jisoo et Rosé, votre charisme et votre passion sont une source d'inspiration pour nous tous.

Aujourd'hui, en célébrant ces sept années incroyables, je tiens à vous remercier du fond du cœur pour tout ce que vous avez offert à vos fans. Votre dévouement, votre talent et votre amour pour la musique résonnent profondément et nous accompagnent dans nos moments de joie, de réflexion et d'émotion.

Tout comme Rosé, j'ai versé une larme en regardant vos vidéos et en ressentant toute l'émotion que vous transmettez. Cela témoigne de l'authenticité de votre art et de la connexion sincère que vous entretenez avec votre public.

En ce jour spécial, je souhaite que les étoiles continuent de briller pour vous, que la musique continue de vous inspirer et que vous puissiez réaliser encore de nombreux rêves ensemble. Que cette septième année soit le début d'une nouvelle ère passionnante pour Blackpink.

Avec tout mon amour et mon soutien,

David M. (Belgium) 🎉🖤💖

author: @michaellim889
text:
Blackpink (Korean: 블랙핑크; RR: Beullaekpingkeu, stylized in all caps or as BLɅϽKPIИK) is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment, consisting of members Jisoo, Jennie, Rosé, and Lisa. The group debuted in August 2016 with their single album Square One, which featured "Whistle" and "Boombayah", their first number-one entries on South Korea's Gaon Digital Chart and the US Billboard World Digital Song Sales chart, respectively.

Kim Ji-soo (Korean: 김지수; born January 3, 1995), known mononymously as Jisoo, is a South Korean singer and actress. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. Outside of her music career, she made her acting debut with a cameo role in the 2015 series The Producers and played her first leading role in the JTBC series Snowdrop (2021–22), for which she won a Seoul International Drama Award.

Jennie Kim (Korean: 김제니; born January 16, 1996), known mononymously as Jennie, is a South Korean singer and rapper. Born and raised in South Korea, Jennie studied in New Zealand for five years before returning to South Korea in 2010. She debuted as a member of the girl group Blackpink, formed by YG Entertainment, in August 2016. In November 2018, Jennie made her debut as a solo artist with the single "Solo". The song was commercially successful, topping both the Gaon Digital Chart and Billboard's World Digital Songs chart. In 2023, she will be making her acting debut in the HBO series The Idol, under the stage name Jennie Ruby Jane.

Roseanne Park (born 11 February 1997), known mononymously as Rosé (Korean: 로제), is a Korean-New Zealand singer and dancer based in South Korea. Born in New Zealand and raised in Australia, Rosé signed with South Korean label YG Entertainment following a successful audition in 2012 and trained for four years before debuting as a member of the girl group Blackpink in August 2016.

Lalisa Manobal (also spelled Manoban; born Pranpriya Manobal; March 27, 1997), known mononymously as Lisa, is a Thai rapper, singer and dancer. She is a member of the South Korean girl group Blackpink, which debuted under YG Entertainment in 2016.

7 anos de blackpink . . . como o tempo passa tão depressa?

author: @dri6548
text:
happy 7th anniversary to the one and only blackpink ✩

hoje é um dia muito especial, não só para mim, mas também como para todo os blinks! o blackpink tá comemorando o seu sétimo aniversário, e eu gostaria de tentar demonstrar, pelo menos um pouco, do meu amor e gratidão através desse texto para as meninas. mas vai ser bem difícil, ainda porque não tem como descrever em palavras tudo o que eu sinto por elas, e também pq eu sou horrível escrevendo textps 

bom, eu realmente admiro muito cada uma das pinks: Jennie, Lisa, Jisoo e Rosé. vocês são muito importantes para mim, e quero agradecer de coração por tudo que já fizeram. vocês me proporcionaram a lembranças incríveis, marcaram minha infância e não teve sequer um dia que me deixaram infeliz. 

às vezes, quando tô vendo alguma edit ou fotos delas, fico pensando nas coisas que elas tiveram que passar e ouvir para chegaram no lugar que estão hoje. mas no final, acabou dando tudo certo e elas conquistaram diversas coisas sozinhas. e todo esse esforço e dedicação valeu muito a pena, pois ganharam diversas premiações, oportunidades e etc. e são consideradas o maior girl group do planeta. elas são simplesmente incríveis.

enfim, parabéns, bp, pelos sete anos de sucesso! vocês são gigantes e merecem todo amor e reconhecimento do mundo. novamente, muito obrigada por tudo. amo vocês 🖤🩷

author: @Kim_maya_my
text:
블랙핑크에게 감사와 고마움을 전하다🩷🖤솔직히 널 알게 됐어 blackpink 노래와 함께 How you like the 💕✨내 말은, 나는 2020년과 2021년의 블링크였다.🤍솔직히 친구 생일파티 갔는데 갑자기 노래가 떠서 내 앞에 여자가 앉아 있어서 누구를 위한 노래냐고 물어봤다그래서 당신은 나에게 말했다 밴드용입니다 blackpink 😍🖤나는 그들의 춤을 보았고 아름다웠다 그리고 집에 왔을 때 🌃노래 검색해서 봤는데 말 그대로 너무 좋았어요 신기했어요 😍💞☺️그리고 더 찾아보니 팬들의 이름 깜박거리다 blink 그 이후로 블링크가 되었고 2년의 공백기를 거쳐서 많이 슬펐습니다. 😭🖤그리고 그해 개인적인 사정으로 심한 우울증을 앓았고 😩그때 내가 제일 좋아했던 노래 gone rose ✨🤍🥹그리고 당신은 나의 지지자이자 가장 좋아하는 사람이었고 또한 당신은 나에게 힘을 주었습니다 내 슬픔과 슬픔을 완성하기 위해 🥹😊예 그래서 그때를 기억할 때마다 그 시련을 어떻게 이겨냈는지 말 그대로 최악의 시기였습니다. 😣솔직히 너무 고맙고 사랑해 너 덕분에 내 모든 두려움을 이겨냈고 지수, 제니, 로제, 리사도 고맙다. 사랑해 행복한 추억 블링크 🥹😊블랙핑크가 Al-Afd를 갱신했으면 좋겠습니다. 갱신하지 않으면 그 이후에 무슨 일이 일어날지 모르기 때문입니다. 😊✨🩷
나는 너희 모두를 사랑해 😊🩷마야는 알제리에서 당신과 함께했습니다 🇩🇿
🩷🇰🇷🩷 maya

author: @Taniahr26
text:
They are so cute! 💗
I just wanted to thank you for everything I went through by your side, throughout these 4 years that I was with you I learned many things from you and the best thing is that we grew together. I laughed a lot, I also cried, I danced, I sang, I made mistakes and I learned; but all of that remains a great experience for me that I certainly would not change for anything. You are my strength and my inspiration, I never really loved a group like I love you but I don't regret anything, more than not having met you since 2016 but I want you to know that maybe I was not with you from the beginning, but I will stay until the end 💗
Thank you for everything Jennie, Lisa, Jisoo, Rosé, you will always have a place in my heart.❤
Here's to many more years with BLACKPINK!...💌❤️‍🩹❤️‍🩹

author: @daintyjennie
text:
As soon as the video ended, I replayed each of their messages to the BLINKs. It made me cry my heart out, and it made me cry a lot when they said, “So, this was BLACKPINK”. I hope their BYE is not their last BYE to everyone. 

BLACKPINK, you are an inspiration to everyone. And no one can be the next BLACKPINK. I know, being an Idol is tough. There are always camera who surrounds you, follows you everywhere, there are threats, there are hard times for the pinks. This time, I won’t hope (but there is still little) that you girls will renew your contract with YG. Despite the mistreatment for the past years, not enough body guards surrounding the members (if they go alone) before. Not giving enough promotions each other comebacks and solos. I hope more better for BLACKPINK in the future but, you girls needed a rest. It’s okay to go on Hiatus, but not for too long. A little more hope is here with me, hoping for them to renew or leave YG . It is the members choice anyway. I love you BLACKPINK, Happy 7th Birthday.🎉

text:
My heart is full! I’m so proud of every single one of you, Jisoo, Jennie, Rosé and Lisa! 7 years felt like 7 weeks! And I remember the first time i saw your music videos and thought to myself how cool you guys are!!! You inspire me to be a successful woman. And i’m so grateful to know you guys! And for Q.18: When i finally got the tickets for born pink concert and thinking is it a dream or reality??? And when i first attended your concert i was really sad because my seat was far away but the encore was so fun that i was about to jump from my far bleachers seat in that site lol! And as if it’s my last i jumped in my seat with my cousin and watching the same fireworks was magical! 
Thank you for being with me in my late teens to my early adulthood. Here for many awesome years with you BLACKPINK! 
Happy 7TH Anniversary fam 🖤🩷
- All my love, Shahad.

author: @blinkstay6747
text:
Happy birthday to us, I give you all lots of love from Belgium. Jennie, jisoo, lisa and rosè I will support you all forever and ever. Blackpink has become my secret place, my second familly and a part of myself over the past few years. It's been a while yet I still recall my first step in this beautifull universe as a baby blink... Little did I know it was gonna take so much place in my life. Before, my life was normal, almost empty but now I have someone to care about and to look up to blackpink has filled my life with color and music and I cant thank them enough. Blackpink became one of my favourites words and being a blink is now more precious than any thing because every time I think about it, I am more and more sure that this is a blessing and I will cherish it. Blackpink is and will always be in my area as this area is my heart. This beating drum that they filled with their music will always be open to them wherever they go and whatever they do.
I LOVE YOU BLACKPINK 🖤💗

Каждых их альбом — это то ради чего стоит жить, всё прекрасно, а клипы — это нечто, ни одна группа не имеет таких прекрасных клипов, хоть их и мало, я о клипах, но они настолько хороши, что каждый раз смотришь, как новый. Мне очень жаль, что девочки подвержены хейту на протяжении всех 7 лет. Очень жаль, что блинки не смогли защитить Блекпинк от волны хейта. Но будем продолжать поддерживать девочек дальше даже, если они не продлят контракт, какой бы деятельностю вы не занялись, знайте: ваши любящие блинки всегда с вами, любят и поддерживают вас. Живите так, как хотите вы, и наслаждайтесь каждым вашим днём) 7 годовщина Блекпинк и Блинков ❤❤❤❤❤❤❤

author: @lizzynogales
text:
HAPPY 7TH ANNIVERSARY BLACKPINK!! Time has passed so quickly since their debut, I still remember when they were introduced as BLACKPINK, I still remember those first lives, those first photos, I have it in my head as such a beautiful memory because thanks to you I am happy and thank you very much for everything I love you a lot during this wonderful time and although I was never able to go to your concerts or get close to you, I realize that you are very nice and sweet people. I still remember how excited I was when they released their solos and even Lisa's solo came out on my birthday, I was so excited, I still watch BLACKPINK HOUSE and I want to live in that house haha, now with BORN PINK MEMORIES I felt as if I was watching all those programs for the first time, I have been your fan for 4 years now and the only thing I regret is not following you since your debut because afterward all my memories of you are magical and very beautiful, you are more than great artists some great people who won my heart, seriously they don't know how much I love them and I would like to go to one of their concerts and buy all the albums. THANK YOU FOR THESE WONDERFUL YEARS I LOVE YOU SO MUCH GIRLS. BLACKPINK+BLINK= FOREVER 🖤🩷
♡

author: @DarkprimeTube
text:
🎉 Happy 7th Anniversary, BLACKPINK! 🎉

Today marks seven years of incredible music, mesmerizing performances, and unforgettable moments with the phenomenal group, BLACKPINK! 🌟🎶 From their debut to becoming global sensations, their talent, charisma, and passion have touched the hearts of millions worldwide.

To the fierce and talented members, Jennie, Lisa, Rosé, and Jisoo, thank you for sharing your extraordinary talents and inspiring us with your music and messages. Your dedication, hard work, and love for your BLINKs have created an unbreakable bond that will last a lifetime. 🌹💖

As we celebrate this milestone, let's remember the countless memories, achievements, and milestones you've achieved together. Your impact on the K-pop industry and music scene is undeniable, and we eagerly await the many more years of success and happiness to come. ✨🌈

BLINKs, it's also a special day for us! Let's continue to support and cherish BLACKPINK's journey as we create even more unforgettable memories together. Spread the love, happiness, and positivity as we commemorate this remarkable day! 🎊🥳

Once again, congratulations BLACKPINK on your 7th Anniversary! Here's to many more years of empowering music and electrifying performances. We love you, and thank you for being a shining light in our lives! 💕🖤
